bilingual.source: Thick clouds cover the top and snow can fall very hard.
bilingual.target: 厚厚的云层覆盖山顶，雪可能会很大。

bilingual.source: Irniq watched the massive shadow weave its way under the thick ice.
bilingual.target: 伊尔尼克看着巨大的影子在厚厚的冰下穿行。

bilingual.source: With water falling off its thick, brown hair, the bear stared back at me.
bilingual.target: 熊的厚厚的棕色毛发上滴着水，它盯着我看。

bilingual.source: Pond skaters can walk on water because of thick, waterproof hairs on their feet.
bilingual.target: 水黾可以在水面上行走，因为它们的脚上有厚厚的防水毛。
考拉有厚厚的灰色毛皮。
这本书有一个厚的封面。
子弹可以穿透厚厚的墙壁。

bilingual.source: She wore a thick coat to keep warm.
bilingual.target: 她穿了一件厚的外套来保暖。

bilingual.source: The sun was occluded by thick clouds.
bilingual.target: 太阳被厚厚的云层遮挡了。

bilingual.source: I like to use a thick quilt in winter.
bilingual.target: 我喜欢在冬天用厚厚的被子。

list.abstract: Thick（英[θɪk]，美[θɪk]），英语单词，作形容词为厚的；密的；茂密的。作名词为最激烈处；最活跃的部分；最密集处。作副词为厚厚地；密集地；浓浓地。短语搭配有thick grass（茂密的草丛）。例句为“But your skin is not nearly so thick as mine.（但是你的皮肤远没有我的厚。）”。 Thick相关副词词性的近义词有deeply、densely，相关反义词有thin、thinly。

yingyinNormal.en: It looks like your uterus is ready for implantation. Oh. I knew it. I knew it. I felt really thick this morning.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你的子宫可以做胚胎移植了。我就知道，我今天早上就觉得厚厚的。

yingyinNormal.en: It’s very thick fog. I can't see a thing.
yingyinNormal.zh: 嗯，这雾非常大。我什么东西都看不见。

yingyinNormal.en: And I thought I ladled the gravy on thick.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我浇的肉汁再厚也没你的脸皮厚。

yingyinNormal.en: You know, for a genius, you can be remarkably thick.
yingyinNormal.zh: 作为天才，你迟钝到家了。

yingyinNormal.en: You have difficulty remembering vocabulary. You have thick accent perhaps.
yingyinNormal.zh: 记单字对你来说很困难，你有很重的口音。

yingyinNormal.en: How? He wouldn't want you if you were thick, now, would he?
yingyinNormal.zh: 怎么会? 如果你很笨他也不会喜欢你，不是吗?

yingyinNormal.en: Even they aren't that thick. But there might be another way.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他们还没笨到那种程度。或许还有别的方法。
yingyinNormal.videoNameEn: 《Harry Potter and the Chamber of Secrets》

yingyinNormal.en: I'm gonna go out the town with these. I just try to coat them as best as I can, as thick as I can.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我要涂这些睫毛出门，所以要尽最大努力涂，越厚越好。

yingyinNormal.en: That's very thick. It is. You can have a taste. It's like brown sauce you put on sausage sandwiches!
yingyinNormal.zh: 非常浓稠。确实，你可以尝一下。像是香肠三明治里面的棕酱。

yingyinNormal.en: And you, you said you weren't coming here, either. I have a thick accent. You don't know what I said.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你，你也说过不来的。我口音重着呢，你根本听不懂我的话。

yingyinNormal.en: An old one. Pre-Blackout. That's gonna be tough. Not much from then. And what's there is thick milky.
yingyinNormal.zh: 老型号的啊。大停电之前的型号。那就麻烦了。那段时间的信息没剩下多少，情况有点复杂。

yingyinNormal.en: Even our shower head is broke, Earl. We got blasted with rusty water and something thick. I feel so dirty.
yingyinNormal.zh: 厄尔，我们家连花洒都坏[破产]了。我们被锈水喷了一身，还有某些不明浓厚东西。我感觉自己好脏。

yingyinNormal.en: Thick as thieves, they were. She tricked the information out of ya, Sean. She used you. Liam, I... Shut up!
yingyinNormal.zh: 一丘之貉，他们是同伙儿。肖恩，她从你口中套出了情报。她利用了你。莱姆，我……闭嘴！

yingyinNormal.en: All you'll need is a pencil, some paper, dry ice, rubbing alcohol, and a spool of 50-micron-thick cobalt-60 wire.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你只需要一支铅笔，一些纸，干冰，外用酒精和一卷50微米细的钴60线轴。

yingyinNormal.en: Rug. What? Well, how could it get broken? The only place for it to fall is the floor and there is a big thick rug.
yingyinNormal.zh: 地毯。什么？这东西怎么会碎呢？唯一的可能性就是掉在地上，而这里却有块厚地毯。

yingyinNormal.en: It's very thick fog. I can't see a thing. Maybe we should go back home. Yes, we'll go to the playground another day. Oh.
yingyinNormal.zh: 今天的雾很大啊！我什么都看不到。我想我们还是回家吧。说得对，我想我们还是改天再去游乐场吧。

yingyinNormal.en: So that when I'm finished, you can still see through those thick pretentious glasses, you psychopathic, unimaginative criminal.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好让我能有耐心说完，你这个带着那副自命不凡的厚眼镜片的、变态的、缺乏创造力的罪人

yingyinNormal.en: Each cell in your body is surrounded by a cell membrane, a thick flexible layer made of fats and proteins, that surrounds and protects the inner components.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你身体里的每一个细胞都是被细胞膜所包起来。那是由脂肪和蛋白质组成的一层即厚又软的物质，包围着并保护着细胞内部。

yingyinNormal.en: It's only when you get closer you realize just how thick this ice is. That's around 20 inches. This is a proper construction project on an industrial scale.
yingyinNormal.zh: 只有凑近了看，你才能发现这冰到底有多厚，大约50厘米厚，这完全是一个工业级的建设项目。

yingyinNormal.en: Fine. I was under a lot of pressure back then, and... Okay, keep in mind I'm not in makeup yet, but do these sandals make my legs look thick? 'Cause I could lower the hem.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，那个时候我承受的压力很大，而且……好了，要记住我还没有化妆，这凉鞋是不是让我的腿显得很粗，如果是的话，我可以把裙边卷下去。

examination_example.sentence: John Gottman, the marriage expert, explains that we quickly "thin slice" information reliably only after we ground such snap reactions in "<highlight>thick</highlight> sliced" long-term study.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 婚姻专家John Gottman解释说，只有当我们在“厚片”的长期研究中对这种快速反应进行磨合后，我们才会迅速可靠地“薄片”信息。

having a very close, friendly relationship
(of a voice) not clear or distinct, especially because of illness or emotion
slow to learn or understand things

word_usage.usage:
thick为不可数名词，through thick and thin表示“不顾艰难险阻”，例：
He's supported the team for over two years through thick and thin.
十多年来,在任何情况下他都支持这个队。

examination_example.sentence: For months the sea is covered with <highlight>thick</highlight> ice.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 几个月来，海洋被厚厚的冰层覆盖着。

examination_example.sentence: I have very <highlight>thick</highlight> fat, so I can keep myself warm.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我有很厚的脂肪，所以我可以使我自己温暖。

examination_example.sentence: But your skin is not nearly so <highlight>thick</highlight> as mine.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但是你的皮肤远没有我的厚。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Thick</highlight> grass and trees and hot winds can easily make fires happen.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 浓密的草和树木和热风很容易使火灾发生。

examination_example.sentence: Both Matt and Martin have <highlight>thick</highlight> and dark hair.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 马特和马丁都有浓密的黑发。

examination_example.sentence: Thousands of years ago, Britain was covered by <highlight>thick</highlight> forests.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 几千年前，英国被茂密的森林所覆盖。

examination_example.sentence: However, blood is much <highlight>thicker</highlight> than water.
Water is about 1, 000 times <highlight>thicker</highlight> and heavier than air.
